Date:  24/3/1875
Source:  Jottings on the Spot
Author:  RIVES
Vol / Page:  16
Edition:
Quote:  I loafed about the station and had a look at the 12,000 wethers they had got in from which they were to draught 7,000 to boil down. After lunch I walked down with W. to look at the boiling down house. ... The boiling down house is about two miles from the homestead to avoid the stench. It is built of galvanised iron.
Notes:

